course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: South American
---

olive oil
1 capsicum
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef strips
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Creole spice blend

• Boil the kettle. Thinly slice capsicum. Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients).
• In a medium bowl, combine Creole spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt. Add beef strips and toss to combine. Set aside.
• In a second medium bowl, add couscous, chicken-style stock powder and a drizzle of olive. Add boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 1 1/2 cups for 4 people) and stir to combine. Immediately cover with a plate and leave for
5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.
• When couscous is done, add baby spinach leaves. Toss to combine and season to taste.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat.
• Cook capsicum and sweetcorn, tossing, until tender and browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Transfer to a medium bowl.

• Return frying pan to a medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Transfer to bowl with veggies. Toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Divide spinach couscous between bowls.
• Top with Creole beef and capsicum.
• Serve with smokey aioli.